# Podman Configuration (alternative to Docker)
# If you are using podman instead of docker, uncomment and configure the line below
# See https://rust.testcontainers.org/features/configuration/#podman-docker-compatibility
# Run `echo $UID` in your terminal to get your user ID, then replace 1000 with your actual UID
# Example: if your UID is 1000, use: unix:///run/user/1000/podman/podman.sock
# DOCKER_HOST=unix:///run/user/1000/podman/podman.sock

# Rust Logging Configuration
# Controls the verbosity of log output for Rust crates using the `log` or `tracing` facade
# Available levels (from least to most verbose): error, warn, info, debug, trace
RUST_LOG=debug
